Gbenga Odogun, Lokoja The Kogi State Governor, Alhaji Yahaya Bello, on Thursday promised to embark on the development of the state, so as to address infrastructural deficit owing to past neglect. Bello said this while inspecting ongoing rehabilitation work on a collapsed bridge within the Lokoja metropolis, which had affected economic activities in the area. The governor said his administration would work hard to deliver good governance to the people, assuring them that the state would witness massive deployment of resources to develop both human and capital projects. Bello maintained that his choice of an experienced professional, Abubakar Ohere, as commissioner for works, underscored his genuine intention to aggressively address infrastructural challenge of the state, particularly in the road and the housing sector. Copyright PUNCH.
